      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be commercially validated with documented QA procedures meeting MRL 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 used with documented software quality assurance procedures. Vendor validation suite confirms solver correctness for turbulent flow applications. QA records maintained per ISO 9001 framework."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification evidence must demonstrate correct numerical implementation for rotating machinery CFD at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification performed via method of manufactured solutions for the governing Navier-Stokes equations. Observed order of accuracy consistent with theoretical second-order convergence. No coding errors identified in the hemolysis power-law damage model implementation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Discretization error estimated and shown to be below 5% for primary QoI at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation applied across three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for normalized hemolysis index is 2.3% on the fine mesh. Spatial discretization error is adequately characterized for the intended COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented and sufficiently representative of the COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "FDA GCBP experimental data collected at five flow-speed combinations spanning the CPB operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM). Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water) used per ASTM F1841. Temperature controlled at 37°C. Test conditions documented in laboratory notebooks and traceable to calibrated instrumentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within 20% across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized hemolysis index compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Maximum deviation is 14.7% at the 3 L/min, 2500 RPM condition. All predictions fall within the 20% acceptance band. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed for the nominal design."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs must directly correspond to the decision-relevant model outputs for hemolysis assessment.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and modified index of hemolysis (MIH) are the primary validation quantities of interest, directly corresponding to the regulatory submission QoIs. Shear stress distributions used as secondary QoI for mechanistic insight. Full alignment between validation and COU QoIs confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on a geometry and under conditions sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the same platform as the COU device. Operating conditions span the CPB clinical range. Blood analog fluid properties match physiological blood viscosity within 8%. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU."
    },
